  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The Respiratory Insufficiency Outcome (RIO) project consists in a french multicenter
      prospective cohort of patients with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) undergoing
      domiciliary noninvasive positive pressure ventilation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
